To prove this inequality, we need to analyze the structure of the stopped process and the hitting time.

The left side is the supremum of the norms of the stopped process up to time `t`. The right side is `K` plus the norm of the stopped value at time `t` (with an indicator function that is `1` if the stopping time is `≤ t` and `0` otherwise).

